event: message_saved
data: {"messageId":"XJGibBnTeoHGbgUVKayxn","role":"user","content":"I need you to perform a complete Kubernetes deployment lifecycle test in the agentic-dev namespace. Do ALL of these steps using MCP tools:\n\nSTEP 1 - CREATE: Use k8s_apply_yaml to deploy a simple nginx pod with this YAML:\n---\napiVersion: v1\nkind: Pod\nmetadata:\n  name: val-test-nginx\n  namespace: agentic-dev\n  labels:\n    app: val-test\n    test: val-02\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: nginx\n    image: nginx:alpine\n    ports:\n    - containerPort: 80\n    resources:\n      limits:\n        memory: 64Mi\n        cpu: 100m\n\nSTEP 2 - VERIFY: Use k8s_list_pods with namespace agentic-dev and label selector 'test=val-02' to verify the pod was created and is running. Wait a moment and check again if it's not ready yet.\n\nSTEP 3 - INSPECT: Use k8s_get_pod to get detailed pod info including IP address and node placement. Use k8s_get_pod_logs to fetch the nginx access log.\n\nSTEP 4 - MODIFY: Use k8s_patch_resource to add an annotation 'validated-by=openagentic-val-suite' to the pod.\n\nSTEP 5 - VERIFY MODIFICATION: Use k8s_get_pod again to confirm the annotation was applied.\n\nSTEP 6 - CLEANUP: Use k8s_delete_pod to remove the test pod.\n\nSTEP 7 - VERIFY DELETION: Use k8s_list_pods again with the label selector to confirm the pod is gone.\n\nReport each step with its result. This is a real deployment lifecycle test - every step must use actual MCP tool calls.","timestamp":"2026-02-20T21:53:42.942Z","source":"database","confirmed":true}

