event: content_block_stop
data: {"index":0,"blockType":"text","finalContent":"---\n\n## Deployment Lifecycle Test — Result\n\n### ❌ All 7 Steps BLOCKED — MCP Proxy is Down\n\nEvery Kubernetes MCP tool call failed with the same error:\n\n```\nError: connect ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080\n```\n\nThis is the **same MCP proxy outage** identified in our previous infrastructure audit. All Kubernetes tools (`k8s_apply_yaml`, `k8s_list_pods`, `k8s_get_pod`, `k8s_patch_resource`, `k8s_delete_pod`, `k8s_cluster_health`) route through the MCP proxy pod at `10.43.224.106:8080`, which is currently **unreachable**.\n\n### Step-by-Step Status\n\n| Step | Operation | Tool | Status | Error |\n|:----:|-----------|------|:------:|-------|\n| 1 | **CREATE** pod | `k8s_apply_yaml` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 2 | **VERIFY** creation | `k8s_list_pods` | ❌ | `ECONNREFUSED 10.43.224.106:8080` |\n| 3 | **INSPECT** pod + logs | `k8s_get_pod` / `k8s_get_pod_logs` | ❌ | Not attempted — dependency on Step 1 |\n| 4 | **MODIFY** annotation | `k8s_patch_resource` | ❌ | Not attempted — dependency on Step 1 |\n| 5 | **VERIFY** modification | `k8s_get_pod` | ❌ | Not attempted — dependency on Step 4 |\n| 6 | **CLEANUP** delete pod | `k8s_delete_pod` | ❌ | Not attempted — dependency on Step 1 |\n| 7 | **VERIFY** deletion | `k8s_list_pods` | ❌ | Not attempted — dependency on Step 6 |\n\n### Root Cause\n\n```diagram\n{\n  \"type\": \"flowchart\",\n  \"title\": \"MCP Proxy Failure Chain\",\n  \"layout\": \"horizontal\",\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\"id\": \"user\", \"label\": \"Lifecycle Test\\n(7 steps)\", \"shape\": \"rounded\", \"color\": \"primary\"},\n    {\"id\": \"proxy\", \"label\": \"MCP Proxy\\n10.43.224.106:8080\", \"shape\": \"hexagon\", \"color\": \"error\"},\n    {\"id\": \"k8s\", \"label\": \"Kubernetes\\nAPI Server\", \"shape\": \"cylinder\", \"color\": \"muted\"},\n    {\"id\": \"cluster\", \"label\": \"agentic-dev\\nNamespace\", \"shape\": \"cloud\", \"color\": \"muted\"}\n  ],\n  \"edges\": [\n    {\"source\": \"user\", \"target\": \"proxy\", \"label\": \"All k8s_* calls\", \"style\": \"solid\"},\n    {\"source\": \"proxy\", \"target\": \"k8s\", \"label\": \"ECONNREFUSED\", \"style\": \"dashed\"},\n    {\"source\": \"k8s\", \"target\": \"cluster\", \"label\": \"Blocked\", \"style\": \"dashed\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Immediate Remediation Required\n\n| Priority | Action | Command |\n|:--------:|--------|---------|\n| **P0** | **Restart the MCP proxy deployment** | `kubectl rollout restart deployment/openagentic-mcp-proxy -n agentic-dev` |\n| **P0** | **Verify proxy pod is Running** | `kubectl get pods -n agentic-dev -l app=mcp-proxy` |\n| **P0** | **Check proxy logs for crash reason** | `kubectl logs -n agentic-dev -l app=mcp-proxy --previous --tail=100` |\n\n> [!WARNING]\n> This is the **same outage** flagged in our previous infrastructure audit. The MCP proxy remains a **single point of failure** — every Kubernetes, admin, Loki, and Flowise tool routes through it. Until the proxy is restored, **zero** cluster management operations are possible through this interface.\n\n### Once Proxy is Restored\n\nRe-run this exact lifecycle test. All 7 steps are ready to execute — the test logic is sound, only the transport layer is down. I will execute each step sequentially with proper dependency chaining:\n\n1. **CREATE** → wait for apply confirmation\n2. **VERIFY** → poll with label selector until `Running`\n3. **INSPECT** → fetch pod details + container logs\n4. **MODIFY** → patch annotation\n5. **VERIFY** → confirm annotation present\n6. **CLEANUP** → delete pod\n7. **VERIFY** → confirm pod gone\n\nLet me know once the proxy has been restarted and I'll re-execute the full suite."}

